column5: message
Merge branch 'master' of github.com:froggey/Mezzano

Merge pull request #132 from ebrasca/fat32

Update Fat32

Change the background GC poll interval.

This prevents the system from being completely trapped in the GC if
the size of the live set exceeds physical memory.
The background GC thread's heuristics need to be improved to take the
size of the live set into account.

Don't allocate/free blocks with a TLB shootdown in progress.

The store functions can call into PAGER-ALLOCATE-PAGE
FAT32: Implement abort-action :delete

PAGER-ALLOCATE-PAGE must not be called with a TLB shootdown in progress.

This can cause deadlocks as all other cores may be spinning on the
shootdown lock and preventing IRQs from being delivered during swap-out.

The effect of this is that other CPUs may see newly mapped wired pages
before the entire mapping request has been completed.
remote: Automatically retry on connection failure.
POST-BOOT-WORKER must decrement *SNAPSHOT-INHIBIT* atomically.

FAT32: Fix allocating new cluster in FAT12 and FAT16

I don't know why it is working with number 3
tcp: Don't allow sending on partially-closed connections.
tcp: Acknowledge FIN packets properly

rtl8168: Fix transmit bugs.

If the transmit ring filled up entirely, then current=tail and no
transmit descriptors would ever be recovered again.
If there were no transmit descriptors available but pending packets,
then the driver would waking up continuously trying to send them.
Improve debug printing of IRQ and SIMPLE-IRQ objects.
cache: fix offset of write-sequence

tcp: Fix listeners listening on 0.0.0.0

The previous behaviour would cause 0.0.0.0 to only bind to the address
of an arbitrary interface.
file-server: Time out idle connections quickly
arp: Fix error when an interface does not have an IP address.
Fix RAISE-STRUCT-TYPE-ERROR

dhcp: Check the XID of the correct packet.

This was checking the XID of the original offer packet, not the ack packet
Fix typos in the RTL8168 driver
The siaddr field must be 0 in DHCPREQUEST packets
cache: Refactor stream-read-byte and stream-read-char
cache: fix writing last byte/char

Support CLASS-PROTOTYPE on BUILT-IN-CLASS

This does not return real instances of the objects, but a fake instance
pretending to have the right class.
Fix (SUBTYPEP (EQL x) (FUNCTION ...))
Fix generic functions with non-standard classes.
Pretty print DEFINE-COMPILER-MACRO
In CONDITION-WAIT-FOR and EVENT-WAIT-FOR return the remaining timeout
Add TIMER-SLEEP.
Refactor WAIT-FOR-OBJECTS, allowing it to be used in supervisor code
Add a :DOCUMENTATION slot option to DEFSTRUCT
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/froggey/Mezzano into fat32

Delay slightly when loading the init file.

This gives network cards time to acquire leases & set up routes.

Catch no route to host errors generated when sending TCP packets.

This can happen if the network configuration changes while packets
are being sent.
Fix (COMPLEX DOUBLE-FLOAT) arrays
DHCP-INVALID-OPTION was overriding the standard CL symbol TYPE.
FAT32: Refactor for better readability
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/froggey/Mezzano into fat32
Enable connection reuse for the remote file system.
Replace the *NICS* list with a WATCHABLE-SET.

Add WATCHABLE-SET.

This is a SET of objects that can be monitored for objects being
added and removed.
Use a generic NAME function instead of per-object NAME functions.
Retransmit must be done with the connection lock held

Specify a connection idle timeout in the remote filesystem.

This stops it from tying up the single-threaded server indefinitely.

Add an inactivity timeout to TCP connections.

This timeout is reset every time a packet is sent or received, if
it expires then the connection is closed automatically.
Typo fix

Fix a race in thread-pool.

Adding a work item at the same time that the last thread in the pool
was exiting would cause the work item not to be run and no new thread
to be created.
Print TCP listeners less verbosely
FAT32: Fix probe-using-host output
FAT32: Split find-file in open-file and open-file-metadata , remove sub-path

Reuse the remote file system's connection to the file server.

This prevents remote FS commands from continuously reconnecting to the
file server and shaves about a minute off of an incremental build.
Not currently enabled by default due to stability concerns.
Signal pending errors in the various TCP stream methods.
*SNAPSHOT-INHIBIT* should be modified atomically.
References
Fix deadlock in snapshot-thread
Send resets for unexpected packets
Notify users properly when a connection is reset.
Support retransmitting the FIN packet when closing.
Retransmit data in :ESTABLISHED
Add support for picking initial send sequence numbers to netmangler.

Send an up-to-date ACK when receiving a non-acceptable segment.

This covers retransmitting the final ack of the three-way handshake.
Rename initial send/receive sequence numbers to match the RFC
Add readers for TCP header fields
Rename window-size to rcv.wnd to match the RFC
Rename s-next/r-next to snd.nxt/rcv.nxt to match the TCP RFC
Fix detection of duplicate SYN packets in :SYN-RECEIVED
Modular arithmetic helpers
Only set PSH on the final segment when sending multiple segments

Add netmangler option to always drop locally-generated TCP packets.

This drops everything but retransmits and ACKs
Make DHCP more robust in the face of duplicate packets
Add netmangler options to duplicate transmitted & received packets.

Use :wait-p nil when receiving network packets.

Sources aren't accurate and there might not be any packets waiting.
Minor cleanup
Set TCP connection state to :CLOSED in DETACH-TCP-CONNECTION
Minor rename

Make retransmit delays clearer.

These should be computed according to the RFCs...
Automatically flush TCP connections opened in previous boots.

Retransmit SYN packets when establishing TCP connections.

Connections now have two dedicated timers, one for general connection
timeouts and one for retransmits.
The :CONNECTION-ABORTED state has been removed and errors conditions
are now created in the stack itself and passed through the connection.
Tools for making the network less reliable.
Export some functions for inspecting dispatch sources
Fix disarming a disarmed timer

Remove support for accepting multiple TCP connections at once.

Not an obviously useful feature.
DHCP option list should be terminated with +OPT-END+

Use ATOMIC-INCF in NEXT-CLASS-HASH-VALUE.

Not replacing every use of %ATOMIC-FIXNUM-ADD-SYMBOL with it yet
because that requires declaiming the symbols as fixnums. That has
bootstrapping issues as PROCLAIM tries to check the types.
Add a wrapper for %%UNREACHABLE
ATOMIC-INCF/-DECF
Use a generic function to dispatch on the ethertype when receiving packets

Support an upper limit for semaphores.

Attempting to increment past this limit will error.
Use NTH-VALUE in GENERIC-REM/MOD
Include the slot name in structure related type errors
Don't call the host's FBOUNDP with CAS function names
Support STREAM-LINE-COLUMN on string output streams
Be more careful when dumping timers.
lldb: Print XMM registers
Support CAS on arbitrary array types
Add float memref accessors
Support CAS for all object-ref & memref accessors

Merge pull request #131 from fittestbits/fittestbits/usb

Fittestbits/usb
Fix bugs in vendor driver and class driver search routines.
Merge device-id class into device class, eliminating the distinction.

Debounce bug fix.

Checked for state change before checking for timeout, so noisy
connection could cause an infinite loop. Moved timeout check to top of
cond.

Simple name changes.

Change (deprecated) get-phys-addr to array->phys-addr.
Change device-disconnect to controller-disconnect.
Change get-word to get-unsigned-word/16 (and add get-unsigned-word/32)

Merge pull request #130 from fittestbits/fittestbits/usb

Minimal USB Driver
Reduce USB logging.
Add test condition around debug code.

Fix bug when disconnecting a device.

Fix confusion between arrays and physical address in loop that removes EDs.

Move USB Driver loading until after the GUI is loaded.

The HID driver depends on a symbol in the GUI package and HID devices
connected before boot will not enumerate without that package.

Serialize hub status change events.

Hub status changes events (connect and disconnect) need to be
serialize because only one device can be mapped to address 0 at a
time.

Fix various bugs.

Improve cleanup in delete-device - it handles cases where there's an
error during enumeration better.

Add lock (semaphore) to device-id to serialize connect and disconnect
to avoid cases where the device structure being updated by multiple
threads.

Fix problem with devices not being recognized on boot.

Generate :hub-status-change event at the end of the OHCI probe code,
so that devics that are already connected (if any) get probed.

Also, use array-element-type instead of type-of.
Convert (eval '(function ... to (compile NIL '(lambda ...

Change all occurances of pci-io-region/16 pci-io-region/32.

Except for two places in usb-debug.lisp which are used for getting and
printing 16-bit items. These routines should never be used unless the
PCI device actually has 16-bit registers.
Change system name from usb to mezzano-usb.

Minimal USB Driver

First USB Driver release, contains:

1. An OHCI (Open Host Controller Interface) driver

2. An USB Driver (Mid-level driver between OHCI driver and device drivers)

3. A HID Class Driver that only supports mice.

Using CL-USER can cause host packages to leak over.
Be more flexible when bringing NICs up/down

Now they use immediate displacements when the index is constant.
Generate wrapper functions for builtins
Remove the old compiler code generator
Add wrapper functions for builtins
Use C-S-F-O from the same package.
Implement a bunch of missing builtins
Implement the %DCAS-OBJECT builtin
Convert tail-called builtins
Move FIXNUM-/CHARACTER-TO-RAW into a more generic place
Fix some declaration warnings
Fix parsing of symbols & characters with escapes in them.
Add BINARY-OUTPUT-STREAM. Like STIRNG-OUTPUT-STREAM but for bytes.
Treat STREAM as a normal class
Add functions for encoding & decoding strings to/from octet vectors
Replace HTTP's TYPE-EQUAL with the one in SYS.INT
Convert recursion in CHECK-DEFINITIONS-DOMINATE-USES to iteration.
Move generic bignum code into a new file

Remove recursion from lengauer-tarjan-dominators.

This was blowing the stack when compiling some particularly large
functions.
Implement NSUBSTITUTE's :COUNT argument
Add default methods for FILE-WRITE-DATA and FILE-AUTHOR
Add type check in NAME-CHAR
Fix printing of arrays when *PRINT-RADIX* is true
Implement :FROM-END for (N)SUBSTITUTE(-IF(-NOT))
Fix DEFTYPE's defaulting behaviour for keyword arguments
Fix truncate on ratios
Split bignum paths out of generic-left/-right-shift
Optimize integer-length
Replace (declare (fixnum ...)) with (declare (type fixnum ...))
Add KNOWN-DECLARATION-P to the cross compiler
Optimize float/bignum comparisons and support NaN/inf
Use EQ for comparing fixnums in =
Don't create intermediate bignums when comparing fixnums & bignums
Fix truncate of large negative floats
Fix fixnum/float comparisons.
Fix conversion of negative bignums to floats
Report unknown declarations when compiling.
Typo fix. Ignoreable => ignorable
Fix a bunch of unused variable warnings
Optimize RATIONAL
Fix conformance issues with float/rational comparisons.
Silence some unused variable warnings
Handle negative zero properly in EQL and when printing.

lldb: Don't print the value of bignums at all.

Printing non-canonical bignums can catastrophic failures.
Improved error reporting
The value of SLOT-MISSING is ignored when called by SLOT-MAKUNBOUND
Check congruence of generic function and method keywords.
Signal a type error with the proper type in CHECK-VECTOR-HAS-FILL-POINTER
Change-class should only initialize instance slots.
Signal invalid initarg errors as program errors
Check lambda-list congruence when reinitializing generic functions

Fix handling of default initargs in constructors

Default initargs must be appended to the end of the initarg list, not
to the start.

Test class-18.1 in ansi-test
Treat :ALLOW-OTHER-KEYS properly in constructor functions
Rename the loop package
Use infinities in loop
Fix spurious warning in DOLIST
Report unused variable warnings for let and let* bindings

Merge pull request #129 from fittestbits/fittestbits/wheelmouse

Add mouse scroll wheel as buttons 4 and 5.

Add mouse scroll wheel as buttons 4 and 5.

Change ps2.lisp mouse configuration to enable scroll wheel input.

Change input-drivers convert mouse scroll wheel input to button 4 and 5 events.
TCP: Allow backlog = nil for indicating an unlimited backlog
TCP: Replace semaphore for integer

TCP: Remove queue from listener

Disable timeout for inbount connections in listener.
TCP: End 3 way handshake before sending connection to listener
TCP: Remove commentary

TCP: End 3 way handshake before continuing connection
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/froggey/Mezzano

Bump LLF version.

Symbol, type, and structure changes are incompatible.
Support :ALLOW-OTHER-KEYS in #S and MAKE-INSTANCE for structure classes
Fix the CHAR-BIT setf expander
Fix CONCATENATE compiler macro when cross-compiling
Add missing space to error messages

Merge COMPUTE-DEFAULT-INITARGS and STD-COMPUTE-DEFAULT-INITARGS

The bootstrapping problems that required that these be separate have
been fixed.
Implement the #S syntax and allow structs to be created with MAKE-INSTANCE
Fix lowering of LIST*
Check types when binding special variables
Return VECTOR instead of ARRAY for vector objects in TYPE-OF
VALUES and non-atomic FUNCTION type specifiers aren't supported by TYPEP
Declaim the types of reader/printer variables.
Implement *PRINT-CASE* :CAPITALIZE

Fix float printing bugs

Floats were printed with two dots when *PRINT-RADIX* was true.
*R-D-F-F* was not being respected properly when set to short-/long-float.
TCP: Refactor tcp-listen
CLASS-OF a non-simple vector should return VECTOR class, not ARRAY.
Signal proper errors in {OPEN,INPUT,OUTPUT,INTERACTIVE}-STREAM-P

Fix bug in ENSURE-CLASS when redefining classes.

If a class with the supplied name exists and the proper name does not
match the supplied name, then a whole new class should be defined
instead of redefining the existing class.
Remove magic numbers from TYPE-OF
TCP: Remove state from tcp4-receive-data
ARP: Update documentation
Support declares properly in the DO-SYMBOLS macros
Signal package errors as PACKAGE-ERROR
Implement UNUSE-PACKAGE

Use TRUNCATE instead of FLOOR in SORT-VECTOR.

TRUNCATE is slightly faster and I-PARENT is never called with a negative
value in way that matters.
Signal type-error when a package isn't found

Remove metering from the compiler.

The profiler & lldb can be used instead.
lldb: Print callers and callees and more detailed instruction counts.
Fix error reporting in /
Fix typo in LIST*, was causing extra consing.
lldb: Print instruction counts as a percentage of total too
Inline %MAKE-HASH-TABLE to avoid the overhead of keyword arg processing.
Remember inline forms for defstruct constructors.
TCP: Port 0 is used to tell the system to find a suitable port number
Update the ARP expiration to using the dispatch API
Improve ergonomics of DEFINE-MODIFY-MACRO

Optimize COPY-LIST & COPY-LIST-IN-AREA.

Avoid the call to COPY-LIST-IN-AREA in COPY-LIST, this allows CONS to
be called directly, slightly faster.
Mark RESULT as dynamic-extent to avoid that allocation.
lldb: Add a mode for reporting number of calls into a function.
Cache the location of C-P-L in BUILT-IN-CLASS
Implement a few missing instruction disassemblers
Add missing LLF opcode name
Fix C&P weirdness in TYPE-SPECIFIER-P
Implement SETF of THE

Optimize BUILT-IN-CLASS-OF

Replace most of the type tests with a lookup table.
Improve LLDB's printing of function names
Cache the location of standard-class's constructor slot
Fix lowering of dynamic extent variables in let bindings.

Refactor symbol-value-cell and %symbol-value-cell-by-cell

%S-V-C-B-C is a more fundamental function, implementing S-V-C using it
makes more sense than the other way around.
Avoid (apply #'concatenate ...)
lldb: Print the funcallable-instance instead of the trampoline.

Sequence optimizations.

Avoid keyword processing in REPLACE.
Optimize LENGTH. I was hoping to avoid this but LENGTH is called
very frequently and the before-optimization path was very slow.
Improve CONCATENATE when the output type is known.
Avoid calling upgraded-array-info twice in make-array
Load LLDB by default and move it into system>
LLDB stuff
Don't log stuff in the register allocator unless logging is enabled.
Fix race condition when stepping over special functions
Add a fast-path for register-only M-V-PROG1
Use the fast instance layout test when testing structure types
Make instance-header more like a real type.
Include the current owner when printing mutexes
Implement %CAS-OBJECT in the new compiler.

Weak pointer vectors.

This is a fixed-length vector-like of weak key mappings.
Roughly the same as a vector full of weak pointers, but more efficient.
Add an early version of make-deferred-undefined-function

Remove the plist slot from symbols.

This reduces their size down from 8 words to 6, hopefully reducing
pressure on the wired area.
Symbol plists are now stored in a separate hash-table

Fix bug when running finalizers.

RUN-FINALIZERS must test if *PENDING-FINALIZERS* is NIL, or it would
pull a random value out of NIL and stuff it into *PENDING-FINALIZERS*.

Convert users of symbol plists over to dedicated hash-tables

Symbol plists aren't thread safe.
Only save the required global value cells when creating the cold image.
Avoid allocating symbol value cells in BOUNDP and MAKUNBOUND

Lazily allocate symbol global value cells.

The vast majority of symbols are never bound. Allocating value cells
for them is very wasteful, as all value cells must be allocated in
the wired area.

Refer directly to symbol global cells whenever possible.

This removes the extra load that referring to the symbol caused.
Avoid allocating frefs in FBOUNDP and FMAKUNBOUND
Give pooled timers useful names
Wrap markers around the debug magic button output

Properly save function fixups when file-compiling.

This fixes a bug where completely invalid entries were being written
into the symbol value cell cache and corrupting the system.
The cache sentinel value was different between images and was saved into
the compiled file. Without fixups to update it when the compiled file
was loaded the old and incorrect value was used.
Protect various important functions from thread pool hijacking

Remove *SERVER-ALIST*

Swank has been updated to use the new listener mechanism, there are no
more users.
Unify the scheduler logic
Improve how tcp-connect implements timeouts.

Have swank specifically listen on 0.0.0.0.

Previously it defaulted to localhost, but this was ignored by the
backend anyway. Be specific in case this is implemented in the future.

Support passing arbitrary hosts to tcp-listen.

This is primarily to support passing "localhost" through as the host.
Implement LOCAL-ENDPOINT for TCP-LISTENER
Fix PACKAGE-SHADOWING-SYMBOLS
Use WAIT-FOR-OBJECTS in telnet instead of using a receive thread.

Add WAIT-FOR-OBJECTS support to TCP streams.

TCP streams become ready when there is data available to be read
Implement local-/remote-endpoint and print-object for UDP connections
Simplify instance scanning slightly.
Move common external-format related methods into a mixin class.

Bump LLF version.

Incompatible data type change.
Optimize checking if an object is an instance or funcallable instance.
Rename sys.gray => mezzano.gray
Expose LISTEN-BYTE and READ-BYTE-NO-HANG

Optimize STANDARD-INSTANCE-ACCESS.

All standard slot locations have type T, so the slower call to
INSTANCE-ACCESS can be replaced with a faster call directly to
%OBJECT-REF-T

Micro-optimize EQL.

Avoid setting up a stack frame and use a slightly smaller instruction
sequence for testing if X & Y are object values.

Fix thread single-stepping on SMP systems.

This was causing duplicate instructions to show up in LLDB traces.

Refactor and enhance external format related code.

External format handing has been unified between the remote fs and
the TCP character streams.
EOL handling can now be configured via extended external formats.
Syntax is (<coding> :eol-style <style>) where <coding> is the coding
system and <style> is one of :lf-ignore-cr, :lf, :cr, :crlf, or :lfcr.
:utf-8 is currently the only supported coding system.
LISTEN and READ-CHAR-NO-HANG have been implemented completely.
LISTEN now returns true only if a complete character is available for
reading, previously it would if only a single byte was available.
READ-CHAR-NO-HANG will return NIL immediately if a complete character
is not available.
PRINT-OBJECT methods for TCP streams & connections.
Clean up slots & accessors in TCP-CONNECTIONS, check slot types.
Add an event for waiting for the current snapshot to complete.
Pause the main network task queue until initialization completes.
Fix peek's network pane

 TCP: Small refactor

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/froggey/Mezzano

Convert the network stack to using the dispatch API.

This doesn't change a whole lot yet, but does remove a few hacks.
TCP: Add multiplexing and demultiplexing
Fix reading of negative ratios.
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/froggey/Mezzano
Update http-demo to use the new dispatch API
libdispatch inspired concurrency API.
Fix creation of funcallable instances with no slots.
Some functions for poking around in the heap.

Fix ROOM's reporting of general/cons area sizes

It was only counting the oldest generation.
Include active TCP listeners in Peek's network pane
Replace TCP-LISTENER's connection list with a mailbox.
#'GC doesn't return a useful value.
Allow objects that support GET-OBJECT-EVENT to be used with EVENT-WAIT-FOR

Fix an early crash bug.

Setting the event-state of prior *BOOT-ID* events could cause threads to
be woken up and this would cause a wakeup IPI to be broadcast to other
CPUs. At this point in the boot process the local APIC hasn't been mapped
in, so the IPI functions were touching unmapped memory and causing an
early page fault.

This only occurred in qemu and not in VirtualBox, presumably due to a
difference in memory maps.
TCP: Small refactor
Add support for WAIT-FOR-OBJECTS to TCP-LISTENER
Add EVENT-WAIT-FOR, along the lines of CONDITION-WAIT-FOR.
Make CONDITION-WAIT-FOR return the first true value of the PREDICATE.
Clarify docstring
Start of a manual
Support structure docstrings.

:DECLARE initarg for generic functions.

Not sure what's up with this.
ENSURE-GENERIC-FUNCTION takes :ENVIRONMENT as a keyword
Work around an issue when building with ECL
Be more careful when defining the generic versions of funcallable-instance-foo
Implement DOCUMENTATION

Improve definition and redefinition of generic functions.

The documentation slot of a generic function was not being set properly.
Generic function redefinition was ignored and didn't work.
Print structure-slot-definitions nicely
Implement SLOT-DEFINITION-DOCUMENTATION
Support unbound slots better in (CAS SLOT-VALUE)

Implement the :TYPE defclass slot option.

Types are checked by (SETF SLOT-VALUE), (CAS SLOT-VALUE), and
writer methods.
Catch tag for terminating thread pool work items
Use CONDITION-WAIT-FOR in obvious places.

Add CONDITION-WAIT-FOR.

This is a macro in the style of C++'s std::condition_variable::wait_for
function to simplify the use of condition variables. It also handles
timeouts correctly over multiple iterations of the loop.
GET-OBJECT-EVENT must always return an event.
Bleh
Fix REMOVE-DUPLICATES when called on a list with a :KEY arg

Fix TCP:WAIT-FOR-CONNECTIONS

CONDITION-WAIT should be used in a loop and the return value indicates
if a normal wakeup or timeout has occurred.

Thread pool implementation.

Threads are spun up and down based on the concurrency of the system
and supplied workload.
Print class-reference objects nicely
Fix a bunch of warnings & typos

Allow the compiler to properly inspect DX lists.

This was breaking optimizations around (apply (lambda ...) ...)
Fix bug in CONDITION-WAIT when a timeout is specified.

Supervisor-side work for thread pools.

These changes allow thread pool to wrap and adjust the behaviour of
blocking functions.
Include the thread's state when printing it.
Add a new option to WITH-MUTEX to support resignalling errors outside the lock
Improve error reporting when wrong types are passed to the sync functions.
Fix some unused variable warnings
Typo
CALL-WITH-WORLD-STOPPED should use UNWIND-PROTECT when calling the thunk

Allow arbitrary values to be used as thread names.

Lists and strings will be copied to the wired area to assist debugging.
Attempt to improve error reporting in PATHNAME and NAMESTRING
Add Patreon link
Replace a call to MAKE-DX-SIMPLE-VECTOR with a DYNAMIC-EXTENT declaration
Replace cross float/int conversion functions with portable implementations
Fix freeing of wired stacks.

Improve support for segment prefixes as part of effective addresses

This allows them to be used in object slot addresses: (:gs :object :rax 1)
Fix stack struct offsets in %CALL-WITH-PROMPT
Fix a race condition when switching threads on SMP systems
Fix early hang when allocating stacks for other CPUs
Make PANIC-PRINT-BACKTRACE more robust
Check that the VM lock is held when doing a TLB shootdown.
The magic button IPI handler must issue an APIC EOI
Reenable SMP support and add a boot option to disable it.
Partially fix a deadlock in thread-final-cleanup

Remove *DEBUG-LINE-LOCK*

This didn't work. Debug-print-line can be called from outside the
supervisor and items to print are not required to be wired.

Alternate arrangements will need to be made...
More sanity checks in IDLE-THREAD
Make the M-F11 magic button slightly more SMP-safe
Fix UNWIND-PROTECT in functions with a closure-allocation declaration.

Reset the preemption timer when quiescing a CPU.

The idle thread does not want to run with the timer enabled.
Add locking to the IRQ code.
More debug messages
Clean up namestring parsing in the remote filesystem.
Don't allow creation of pathnames with a NIL host component.
Fix virtio-net IRQ handling.
LAPIC timer state must be per-cpu.
Include the condition when panicing via ensure
Lock around DEBUG-PRINE-LINE-1 to prevent CPUs interleaving messages.
Add timeout support to condition-wait
Fix typo in timer-expired-p
Add a lambda-list definition to %C-O-W-S-W-I

Moving towards CCL support for cross-compilation

This doesn't work yet, CCL understandably dislikes what %DEFSTRUCT does.

Merge pull request #120 from ebrasca/master

Updates for network
Ethernet: Better and less verbose debug text
Fix DNS lookup
TCP: Don't format debug information
TCP: Manage receiving out of order packets
TCP: Don't write packets, it just make compilation slower
TCP: Don't write information when geting duplicated SYN packets in :syn-received state
TCP: Send RST and detach when closing connection in :syn-sent state
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/froggey/Mezzano
TCP: Fix sending data in :close-wait state
TCP: Add documentation for tcp4-receive
Merge branch 'master' of github.com:froggey/Mezzano

Bump the LLF version

The changes to the symbol cache and for wait-for-objects break
compatibility.

(defun lastcar (list)
  "Returns the last element of LIST. Signals a type-error if LIST is not a
proper list."
  (declare (notinline car cdr))
  (do ((last list fast)
       (fast list (cddr fast))
       (slow (cons (car list) (cdr list)) (cdr slow)))
      (nil)
    (when (not fast) (return (cadr last)))
    (when (not (cdr fast)) (return (car fast)))
    (when (eq fast slow) (circular-list-error list))))

Add new structure options.

:SEALED is a structure option that prevents the structure from being
included in substructures.
:ALIGN is a slot option that controls slot alignment in memory. Slots
can be aligned to 1, 2, 4, 8, or 16 bytes and will always be at least
naturally aligned.
:FIXED-VECTOR is a slot option that defines the slot as a vector embedded
directly in the structure. :TYPE defines the element type of the vector.
Fixed-vector slot accessors take an index argument to index into the
vector, they don't return the vector itself.

Merge branch 'master' of github.com:froggey/Mezzano

Fix hash-table iteration.

If a hash-table was being iterated over and accessed through GETHASH
then a GC cycle could cause the iterator to lose track of the current
position. GETHASH after a GC will rehash the hash-table, which creates
a new hash-table storage vector with a potentially different layout.
The iterator's index would not be valid in this new storage vector.

The hash-table iterator has been modified to always use the original
storage vector, not the current.

This was causing the compiler to miscompile code.

could cause deadlocking if another thread was attempting to acquire
after the world had been resumed.

Pages can now be marked wired and the block map is loaded by the bootloader

and where to load them from, so passing it over to the pager prevents
the pager from having to redundantly load it.

will pave the way to more flexible use of the address space.

&CLOSURE is the function object the function was invoked through when

This requires a host that supports them, such as SBCL or Mezzano.
Fix a bunch of undefined variable warnings.
Implement an undefined variable warning.
Code generator & builtins are architecture specific.
Add an architecture field to the image header.
Extract x86-64 specific parts of the cold-generator into a seperate file.
Add an architecture field to the LLF header.
Use cross-features when reading #+/#- instead of the host features.
Merge the lispos and lispos-compiler systems.
Move LAP into the compiler subdirectory.
Mention the new German keymap in the readme.

Added German keymap
Added German keymap
KP-Divide should map to /, not to \.
Swank listens on port 4005, not port 4007.
Report a warning when the file server address is set to localhost.

Fix :DEFAULT-INITARGS.

Default initargs weren't being computed properly when no initargs were
passed to MAKE-INSTANCE.
This also fixes an error when starting MED.
Improve error reporting when parsing invalid IPv4 addresses.
Save supervisor messages to a log buffer.

Implement STREAM-LINE-COLUMN for the cold-stream.

It isn't accurate, but good enough to make ~& work in XP again.
Only read floats that have either a decimal point or exponent marker.
Spin on the world lock instead of blocking on it.
Make allocation failures into continuable errors.
Print more information in the panic backtraces.

Clean up thread run queues.

Replace the old head/tail variables with objects for each run queue, and
add a new :supervisor priority level for threads that run even with the
world stopped (such as the pager).
Implement READ-DELIMITED-LIST.
Move readtable initialization code into a function.
Implement keyword args for union/intersection/set-difference.

Bump the LLF version.

Changes to symbols and the package system are not backwards compatible.
Support running the file-server on some 10/8 networks.

Ignore macro and destructuring-bind variables named NIL.

This fixes (destructing-bind (() &body body) ...).

Replace DEFVAR with DEFGLOBAL throughout the supervisor.

This should fix all the panics caused by wired code trying to look up
symbol value cells on non-wired stacks.

Improve how special variables and constants are handled.

This introduces DEFGLOBAL, for declaring a special variable that cannot
be bound over. This avoids a lookup when accessing the symbol's value,
which is important in the supervisor.
Constants can no longer be let-bound over, the compiler signals an error.
There is optional support for SBCL-style defconstant checking, to prevent
constants from being redefined with different values.
Use SYMBOL-GLOBAL-VALUE in the serial debug driver.
Save DOUBLE-FLOATs properly when natively file-compiling.

Pass arguments to %DEFPACKAGE using keywords.

This should make it less fragile when more arguments are added.
Use local nicknames in the desktop.
Implement SBCL-style package-local nicknames.
Swank is started automatically now.
Remove the old README.

Make the Readme look nicer

Automatically start the Swank server.

Now that the multithreaded communication style works reliably, it's
fine to have running in the background.
Update full-eval to use the new environment objects & functions.
Fix cross %DOUBLE-FLOAT-AS-INTEGER. Was breaking on negative floats.
Implement MAKE-LOAD-FORM for complex objects.

Fix bugs when printing lists shortened by *PRINT-LEVEL*.

Single element lists weren't printing the closing ).
Dotted lists should always print the dotted element.
Don't do SETQ constant back-propagation on captured variables.
Add more ignorable functions to the profiler.
Switch to a more accurate implementation of SIN/COS.
Check that block & go-tag names have the correct type.

Fix MACROLET at the top-level of a compiled file.

DEFUN forms within a top-level macrolet were incorrectly being
compiled in the null lexical environment.
Fix ~R when printing numbers in cardinal/ordinal form.
Preserve array/vector element-types when saving them to compiled files.
Accept regular environment objects in compile-lambda.
Remove the cross-compiler's dependency on ITERATE.
Convert ASDF systems to serial dependencies.
Switch to multithreaded Swank.
Early CERROR.

Fix dynamic-extent closure bug.

(let ((foo (frob)))
  (lambda (bar)
    (zod (dx-lambda ()
           (list bar foo)))))

The environment vector containing FOO would incorrectly be allocated
dynamic-extent, even though the outer lambda has indefinite extent.
Support integer ranks as dimension-specifiers in array types.
Avoid errors when interning keywords.
Obey *READ-SUPPRESS* when reading ## and #=

Broadcast when notifying *WORLD-STOP-CVAR*.

If multiple threads were waiting on the condition variable to go PA, then
only one of them would be woken after the world resume, leaving them
hanging and occasionally locking up the rest of the system.
Run the GC in a separate thread with a larger stack.

INTEGER-DECODE-FLOAT and FLOAT-SIGN.

This is needed for TRUNCATE to work on large floats.
Bignum to float conversion.
Remove debug message.

Use SINGLE-/DOUBLE-FLOAT-AS-INTEGER in describe.

Grovelling around directly in the single-float representation using
LISP-OBJECT-ADDRESS doesn't work, as this shifts the float's high bit
away.
Utility functions for inspecting closures.

Use the global value of *INTERRUPT-SERVICE-ROUTINES*.

This was causing nested page faults during panic when the stack was
not yet paged in.
Signal an error if an constant is modified.

Improve how lexical environments are handled throughout the system.

This replaces the old environment lists with a lexical-environment
object that is managed through a new, less ad-hoc protocol.
A bunch of bugs relating to the scoping of SPECIAL and NOTINLINE
declarations have been fixed.
Symbol macros (both DEFINE-SYMBOL-MACRO and SYMBOL-MACROLET) should
work properly now.

C-M-Esc in the compositor to break using CERROR instead of BREAK.

BREAK rebinds *DEBUGGER-HOOK* to NIL, which disables SLDB.
Include the pathname host in NAMESTRING.

Re-enable the loopback network interface.

This was disabled for testing, and was comitted by mistake.
Added MBuild reference installation section
Update README.md

actually fixed this time

This is my attempt at making the github readme easier to read for incoming people. I am one of those people who found out about your project from browing github, and I hope that this newer page will make this project more interesting for them.
fixed errors
fixed my mistakes
Made the README prettier
Parse the parameters to ~A/~S.
Implement ADJUST-ARRAY's :INITIAL-CONTENTS argument
Fix SQRT on non-floats.

Implement fixnum division by -1.

Special casing required due to overflow when dividing MOST-NEGATIVE-FIXNUM
by -1.
Implement FFLOOR/FCEILING/FROUND/FTRUNCATE.

Fix BINARY-+ on non-fixnums.

If the LHS was used after the call and either operand was not a fixnum,
then the LHS value would not be spilled properly, causing it to become
NIL in some cases.

Fix deadlock in call-with-pseudo-atomic/-world-stopped.

Having two condition variables was an attempt to avoid PA threads from
being starved out when many threads wanted to stop the world.
Hide the closure environment variables from the debugger.
Grow the pinned area when it is full.
Implement COLD-LISTEN.
Add a magic button (left meta + F11) to backtrace all threads.
Use finalizers to release memory used by thread stacks.

Fix multiple finalizers running during a single GC.

The finalizer lists were being mismanaged, causing completed finalizers
to be run multiple times.
Unbreak XP.
LET bindings still need to be performed, even if control terminates.
Replace a call to EVAL in XP with a regular closure.
Fix the COMPLEX type when used as a bare type.
Avoid recursively calling the compiler when compiling format strings.
XP's PPRINT-DISPATCH class conflicts with the CL symbol.
Improve error handling around generic functions.
Make types more correct.
Fix simple-strings.
Signal the right kind of error in COERCE-TO-CONDITION.
Signal an error when a simple-condition with no format control is reported.
Track load pathnames in eval.
Check DEFCLASS class options & slot definitions more thoroughly.
Send correctly sized ARP and ping response packets.
Accept IP address designators in NET-SETUP.

Fix name conflict in RTL8168 driver.

The WORKER slot in the RTL8168 struct was conflicting with the
RTL8168-WORKER function.
Improve SUBTYPEP on types that are classes.
Don't fold infinite loops into themselves.

Follow the rule of float substitutability in SQRT.

A non-float argument produces a single-float result, no a double-float.
Implement UPGRADED-COMPLEX-PART-TYPE.
Wire up specialized float & complex arrays.
Hash double-floats properly.
#\Delete/#\Rubout is non-graphic character.

Fix character types, BASE-CHAR and STANDARD-CHAR.

These were failing when tested against non-character objects.
Fix FLOAT when no prototype was passed.
Implement specialized complex types.
Fix %INTEGER-AS-DOUBLE-FLOAT when the argument is a bignum.
Fix %OBJECT-REF-(UN)SIGNED-BYTE-foo when the index was constant.
Implement DOUBLE-FLOATs.
Fix WITH-PAGE-FAULT-HOOK.
Partially implement included defstruct definitions.
Process the exponent type properly when reading floats.
Copy DECODE-UNIVERSAL-TIME from SBCL.
Don't perform dotted list processing when *READ-SUPPRESS* is active.
Fix MULTIPLE-VALUE-BIND when binding special variables.

Parts of the supervisor need to use the global values of some symbols.

Now that symbol-value involves searching the special stack, code that
runs in interrupt/exception handlers must use symbol-global-value to
avoid touching memory that can potentially be swapped out.
Implement PHASE.
Implement concatenated streams, currently characters only.
Fix PEEK-CHAR when peeking near EOF.
STANDARD-METHOD should inherit from METHOD.
Implement LCM.
Fix the lambda-lists of ALLOCATE-INSTANCE and MAKE-INSTANCE.

Define the floating point error conditions.

These are never signalled, as there's no way to enable IEEE float
exceptions yet.
Remove the :TEST from the MUFFLE-WARNING restart established by WARN.
Implement SUBST/-IF/-IF-NOT.

Don't error when TYPEEXPAND-1 is passed a non-symbol/non-list.

This can happen a call to TYPEP is compiled with a constant type argument.
(TYPEP foo #<Built-In-Class SYMBOL>)
Implement REMF.
Only print vectors & bit-vectors specially when *PRINT-ARRAY* is true.

Add a cache for symbol binding cell lookups.

This largely eliminates the slowdown from deep binding, with the cache
having a hit rate of around 90-95%.

The cache is a 128 entry array stored directly in the thread object,
replacing the old TLS array. It is currently index by the low bits of
the symbol address, but this could be replaced by any hash for the symbol.
The cache is updated when there is a miss, when a special variable is
bound (a recently bound special variable will probably be accessed soon),
and when a binding is undone (because it is no longer valid).

This currently relies on the fact that symbols and their value cells
are wired. Changes to the GC and cache index will be needed if
this changes.
MAKUNBOUND returns the symbol.
Remove all references to the TLS area and symbol TLS values.
Add another network configuration check.

Switch to deep binding for special variables.

This slows symbol-value down somewhat, but allows an unlimited number
of special variables to be bound.
Fix handling of v format parameters in ~R,~D,~B,~O, and ~X.
ADJOIN's key parameter may be NIL.

Panic when TLS slots are exhausted.

Trying to signal an error just leads to the system panicing anyway.
Implement :ALLOW-OTHER-KEYS for compiled functions.
Split compiler/compiler.lisp into a few separate files.
Fix displaced strings.
Only use the primary value return by SLOT-UNBOUND.
Try to load init.lisp from the home directory on boot.
Test network and file-server connectivity during first boot.
Add a QUIET option to PING-HOST and make it return a success value.
Signal errors when a TCP connection fails to connect.

Implement WITH-CONDITION-RESTARTS and fix restart filtering.

Restarts are only counted when they are associated with the condition
and their test passes, not or.
Print a fresh line before TIME's report.

Rework how function names are parsed in FUNCTION-REFERENCE.

Now a type error is raised properly when the name is something like
(SETF . BAR).

Avoid using FORMAT in GENTEMP.

This was causing calls to GENTEMP to indirectly bump *GENSYM-COUNTER*.
STRING-INPUT-STREAM and STRING-OUTPUT-STREAM derive from STRING-STREAM.
Hackishly support ~< ~> in XP's FORMAT.
Don't let the format string function cache grow uncontrolled.

Always return OBJECT from WRITE.

Do this instead of relying on WRITE-PRETTY or WRITE-OBJECT.

Refactor WRITE-OBJECT and fix printing of complex numbers.

Complex numbers were having their real & imaginary parts printed on
the wrong stream.
Implement LOGCOUNT and CONJUGATE.
Signal the right kind of error when too few arguments are passed to a generic function.
Call SLOT-MISSING in the SLOT-VALUE-USING-CLASS methods for structures.
SLOT-UNBOUND's default method should signal UNBOUND-SLOT.

Fix keyword argument suppliedp values when the function is inlined.

They were always being bound to NIL, no matter if the keyword was
supplied or not.
Set :ARGUMENT-PRECEDENCE-ORDER properly for DOCUMENTATION.

Fix EQUALP when comparing hash-tables.

The test for structure-object was before the test for hash-tables,
causing hash-tables to always be compare as regular structures instead
of as hash-tables.
Implement CHARACTER and CHAR-NOT-EQUAL.
Fix DEFPARAMETER, must evaluate to the symbol name, not to 'NAME.
Implement CCASE and CTYPECASE.

Avoid using +PHYSICAL-MAP-BASE+ directly when possible.

Replaced with CONVERT-TO-PMAP-ADDRESS, or with physical-memref-foo.
Implement the LOGICAL-PATHNAME function.
Implement the &ENVIRONMENT argument for MACROLET functions.

Fix bugs in %OBJECT-REF-/MEMREF-SIGNED-BYTE-64.

%OBJECT-REF-SIGNED-BYTE-64 was not boxing 64-bit values properly
(SETF %OBJECT-REF-/MEMREF-SIGNED-BYTE-64) were not checking types
properly, leading to type errors when storing bignums.

Fix %COERCE-TO-CALLABLE when called with an funbound symbol.

The undefined function thunk is stored in the function slot when
an function-reference is funbound, not nil.

Fix parsing of dotted lists when there's a space after the final item.

"(foo . bar )" is read correctly now.
Support class objects as TYPEP type-specifiers.
Fully implement MAKE-ARRAY's INITIAL-CONTENTS parameter.
MACROLET and SYMBOL-MACROLET definitions are visible in MACROLET bodies.
DEFSETF long form wraps a BLOCK around the body.

Implement ## and #= in the reader.

Circular objects not supported yet.
Support the :DECLARATIONS initarg for generic function metaobjects.
Replace IPL paths with logical pathnames.
Logical pathnames.
Fix misnamed variable. +BLOCK-MAP-ID-DEFERRED+ => +BLOCK-MAP-ID-LAZY+
Implement %VALUE-HAS-TAG-P, which tests the tag of a value.
Never inline functions when a builtin is available.

Only print GC debug messages when *GC-ENABLE-LOGGING* is true.

As virtual serial ports are so slow, this has a noticeable impact on
GC times.

Lazily allocate disk blocks.

Disk blocks are now only allocated when a page is going to be swapped
out or written back to disk as part of a snapshot.
This improves GC performance somewhat, as the pager no longer needs to
call the slow store free functions when releasing memory in most cases.
Extract code related to examining block map entries into functions.
Phrase an error message better.
Implement SUBSETP.
Give natively compiled toplevel form lambdas names.
Fix typos.
Remove some special cases from the CLOS code.
Call COMPUTE-EFFECTIVE-METHOD from COMPUTE-EFFECTIVE-METHOD-FUNCTION.

Accept loop iteration forms after body forms with a warning.

This isn't standard, but some code needs it.

Implement COMPUTE-SLOTS properly.

This splits the old STD-COMPUTE-SLOTS in to the primary method, which
computes the list of effective slots, and the around method which
computes their layout.

Fix DEFAULT-DIRECT-SUPERCLASSES.

It needs to work on subclasses of (FUNCALLABLE-)STANDARD-OBJECT as well.
Remove special cases and unconditionally call VALIDATE-SUPERCLASS.

Improve slot access.

The SLOT-foo-USING-CLASS generic functions are now correctly passed
the effective slot, instead of the slot name.
The SLOT-foo functions will invoke SLOT-MISSING when a slot is missing
from a class in some cases. They currently do not call it when the
class is a STD-CLASS.

Rename STANDARDISH-CLASS-P to STD-CLASS-P.

Properly default direct-superclasses when initializing class metaobjects.

Additionally, remove the non-MOP path from ENSURE-CLASS and just call
ENSURE-CLASS-USING-CLASS.
Merge some methods together using the new class hierarchy.

Completely rework how CLOS is bootstrapped, to improve MOP compliance.

All metaobjects have been defined now, and have the correct
inheritance hierarchy.
Slot definitions are now represented using their proper classes, and
the proper classed for effective and direct slot definitions are used now.
The :argument-precedence-order option for generic functions has been
implemented.
The DIRECT-/EFFECTIVE-SLOT-DEFINITION-CLASS generic functions have been
implemented and are used properly.
The lambda-list of COMPUTE-EFFECTIVE-SLOT-DEFINITION has been corrected.
Write up fresh-line-related bug in XP.
Implement DIGIT-CHAR.
Rename the SYSTEM.CLOSETTE package to MEZZANO.CLOS.
Fix KLUDGE-ARGLIST with &AUX variables.
Implement coercing a lambda-expression to a function.
Implement STRING-CAPITALIZE and NSUBSTITUTE-IF-NOT.
Make COMPUTE-APPLICABLE-METHODS(-USING-CLASSES) generic.
CLASS-PROTOTYPE.
Implement VALIDATE-SUPERCLASS.
Implement SINGLE-FLOAT(-NEGATIVE)-EPSILON. Values from SBCL.

Closette cleanups.

Remove APPLY-METHOD, APPLY-METHODS, and APPLY-GENERIC-FUNCTION.
Move KLUDGE-ARGLIST into macros.lisp.
Fix EXTRACT-LAMBDA-LIST. It was putting &OPTIONAL params in the wrong place
Implement the long form of DEFSETF.
Export EXTRACT-LAMBDA-LIST and EXTRACT-SPECIALIZER-NAMES.
Implement incomplete and forward-referenced classes.

Fix the class precedence list of STANDARD-CLASS & co.

STANDARD-CLASS and FUNCALLABLE-STANDARD-CLASS now have CLASS,
SPECIALIZER, and METAOBJECT in their class precedence lists, as
specified by MOP.
BUILT-IN-CLASS has been implemented, and classes for built-in objects
now use it as their meta-class.
A new class, CLOS-CLASS, has been introduced to unify the slot
definitions for the foo-CLASS metaclasses.
Write to the correct stream in DESCRIBE-OBJECT.

Improve CLOS user interface macros.

They now follow AMOP and the CL spec more closely.
The METACLASS and DIRECT-SUPERCLASSES options to ENSURE-CLASS now
accept class metaobject names as well as class metaobjects.
Class direct-default-initargs are now represented correctly as a list of
lists of initargs, initform and initfunction.

Improve Closette boostrapping.

The bootstrap code has been moved into a function and is only run
when Closette.lisp is loaded for the first time.
This is a step towards allowing Closette to be reloaded, without
hosing any existing classes/generic functions/methods.
Hash numbers properly in EQL-HASH.

Use *PRINT-LENGTH*, not *PRINT-LINES* when printing ";; Loading [...]"

*PRINT-LINES* was causing the message to lose its trailing newline,
causing the loading messages to stack up.

Signal an error when FORMAT was called with an unsupported control string.

Previously it would go into infinite recursion failing to compile the
control string and attempting to fall back on FORMAT.

Print escaped symbols more nicely.

Use the multiple escape characters to escape the entire symbol instead
of escaping each symbol individually.
Include XP in the cold image, and make it the default format implementation
Always compile format strings, don't use EVAL.

Small cleanups.

Change DESCRIBE-XP to a DESCRIBE-OBJECT method and use
PRINT-UNREADABLE-OBJECT to print XP streams.
Replace GET-PRETTY-PRINT-STREAM and INITIALIZE-XP with MAKE-INSTANCE
and an INITIALIZE-INSTANCE method.
Use *PRINT-LEVEL* and *PRINT-LENGTH* when loading from Lisp source files.
Implement *PRINT-LEVEL* and *PRINT-LENGTH*.
Inherit XP-STRUCTURE from FUNDAMENTAL-CHARACTER-OUTPUT-STREAM.

Add a stream argument to FORMAT-foo.

They were printing on *STANDARD-OUTPUT*, which wasn't bound to the
XP stream.
Don't use FORMAT in GENSYM.
Implement basic format directives directly, instead of calling CL:FORMAT.

Expose various format interpreters as ordinary functions.

This allows XP to call them directly instead of via CL:FORMAT.
Fix accidental introduction of multiple-value-setf.
Print &env parameter properly when printing compiler ASTs.
SETQ => SETF.
Move functions and macros into their proper files after splitting.
Store symbols, not functions, in the pprint dispatch table.
Split XP into multiple files.

Fix compiler bug.

Stack slots allocated for DX objects were at risk of being doubly
allocated.
Untabify xp.lisp.
Remove page break characters.
Replace structs with classes, and #. with defconstant.
Twiddling with FORMAT.
Integrate XP better. Not finished, but functional.
Default implementations of STREAM-LINE-COLUMN/-LENGTH.
Add xp-code.lisp from ftp://ftp.sunet.se/pub/lang/lisp/code/io/xp/xp.tgz
Bump the size of the pinned area.

Bump LLF version.

Changes to the package system are probably incompatible.
Move Closette into a subdirectory of system/
Treat an element-type of :DEFAULT as CHARACTER.
Signal proper FILE-ERRORs when file errors occur.

*LOAD-PATHNAME* and *LOAD-TRUENAME* must be bound to pathnames.

LOAD-LISP-SOURCE was binding them directly to streams, which can be
coerced to pathnames, but are not actually pathnames.
Implement slots with :class allocation.
Fix SUBTYPEP when type-1 is a class.
Fix performance in FIND-SYMBOL with deep package graphs.
Partially implement PACKAGE-SHADOWING-SYMBOLS.
Accept :UTF-8 as an external format when opening character files.
Fix REDUCE when called with FROM-END.
LOOP's BLOCK must cover the entire loop.
Print method combinations as part of generic functions.
Export MUTEX-HELD-P, ACQUIRE-MUTEX, and RELEASE-MUTEX.

Implement method combinations.

This is largely complete, however the :ARGUMENTS option to
DEFINE-METHOD-COMBINATION hasn't been implemented and generated
effective methods may not be particularly efficient.
Implement NO-APPLICABLE-METHOD.

Extract the transport path in transport-object into a separate function.

This allows the profiler to differentiate between truly transporting
an object and just following an existing forwarding pointer.
Parse the :shadowing-import-from option to defpackage.
Use a log function instead of testing *PAGER-NOISY* directly.
Implement SIMPLE-BIT-VECTOR-P.
Print % of total/direct counts in the profiler report.
Loading a structure definition from a compiled file defines that structure.
Improve structure slot equality in the code-generator.

Simplify CHECK-STRUCT-TYPE.

Correcting errors is expensive and not all that useful.
Move contested path out of the main body of RELEASE-MUTEX.

Remove type & bounds checking from %struct-slot.

Types should have been checked long before reaching here.

Rename the worker slot in virtio-net.

It was conflicting with the virtio-net-worker function.
Inline struct accessors.
Print backtraces for all threads when panicking.
Optimize structure-type-p.
Merge (cas %struct-slot) and %cas-struct-slot.

Improve mutex release fast path.

Now release can avoid disabling interrupts when the lock is not contested.

Don't generate a function for SYS.INT::READ-FRAME-POINTER.

Calling it through a function will return the frame pointer of that
call, not the frame pointer of the caller.
Give better names to UNWIND-PROTECT cleanup functions.
Determine lambda names during pass1, not late in the compile.
Implement NOTINLINE for FLET and LABELS.
Inline the store freelist metadata accessors.
Cache FIND-CLASS result in BUILT-IN-CLASS-OF.
Bind *LOAD-TIME-VALUE-HOOK* in fast-eval.
Fix binding of *LOAD-TIME-VALUE-HOOK* in X-COMPILE.
Use %OBJECT-OF-TYPE-P instead of testing tags directly.
Optimize array type checking.
Prune some internal functions from profiles.
Reimplement BINARY-=/</<=/>/>= in Lisp.
Replace ASH with separate functions for left & right shifts.

Replace CURRENT-THREAD with a fast assembly implementation.

This new version stores a pointer to the thread in the thread object
itself, allowing the current thread to be retrieved quickly through a
GS segment read and avoiding a very expensive MSR read.

Limit the PIT divisor when the tick rate is very low.

The PIT has a minimum rate of about 18Hz. Below this the divisor is
too large to fit in the 16-bit divisor field and would overflow.

Optimize STORE-INSERT-RANGE a little.

This is where the GC seems to be spending a large chunk of time.
Optimize STRUCTURE-TYPE-P a little.

Take profile samples from the area allocation functions.

This allow the profile report to show which areas are allocated from
the most.
Add window size parameters to Mandelbrot.
Add sanity check to RETURN-ADDRESS-TO-FUNCTION.

Tail call in %APPLY when possible.

It's polluting my profiler stack traces.
Remove the obsolete sys.int::%allocate-object function.

Allow streams to display arbitrary objects.

Currently only the text-widget does anything. It displays surfaces.
Don't call EXPT in EMIT-IMM.

Add benchmark function to Mandelbrot.

Renders to a surface instead of a window.

Allocation profiler.

This takes a sample of the current thread every time an allocation
function is called.
Improve the profiler report.
Allow status lights to be positioned at the top or bottom of the screen.
Optimize THREADP and SET-LIGHT.

Fix GC metadata in %CALL-ON-WIRED-STACK-WITHOUT-INTERRUPTS.

The frame is torn down after RBP is popped, not when RSP is restored
to the original stack.

This bug never triggered because sti inhibits hardware interrupts over
the next instruction (which had the incorrect metadata), and the chance
of the stack being paged out is very slim.
Only scavenge live MV area slots.
Add more debug messages to load.
Trying to fix sporadic DEFCONSTANT errors when loading the compiler.

Fix case-changing when characters don't have an othercase character.

The character LATIN SMALL LETTER SHARP S is lower-case but has no simple
(single character) uppercase equivalent. CHAR-UPCASE was incorrectly
returning #\Null for it & similar characters.
Point BUILD at the new build system.
Avoid early defconstant errors from SBCL.

Encode the Unicode General_Category field in Unicode info and use it.

GRAPHIC-CHAR-P and ALPHA-CHAR-P are now finally Unicode-aware.
Replace Unicode info related magic numbers with defconstants.

Fix cross-compiled byte specifiers in data-types.lisp

Defconstant byte specifiers in data-types.lisp were calling BYTE
before it was loaded from cross-compile.lisp. Move it into cross.lisp
so it is ready early.
Latest version of CL-JPEG is thread safe. Remove the lock.
Use jump tables for case when possible.

Turn small byte specifiers into immediate objects.

This allows them to be used in DEFCONSTANT, which should make writing
drivers slightly nicer.
Untabify constprop.lisp.
Split keymaps into their own file & improve keymap switching.

Make PUSHNEW cross-compilation safe again.

 #'identity was being evaluated by the cross-compiler host, producing a
host function instead of a cross function.
